BELGRADE, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Montenegro on Thursday declared four Russian diplomats as "persona non grata". "A formal note on this decision, which sets a seven-day deadline for leaving the territory of our country, was handed to the Russian ambassador today," the ministry said in a press release. On March 4, Montenegro expelled one Russian diplomat, giving him 72 hours to leave the territory. On March 24, one Montenegrin diplomat in Moscow was declared "persona non grata".  â– 